                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Rejig splits Texmaco 
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                          Poddar: Tweak time                                  
	Calcutta, Sept. 27: Wagon manufacturer Texmaco Ltd has restructured its business and its board following an approval from Calcutta High Court.        
	The entity will be split into two. The core engineering business will be transferred to a new company  Texmaco Rail amp; Engineering Ltd  while Texmaco will have the investments, real estate and hydro power divisions in its fold.        
	Shareholders of Texmaco will get an equal number of shares in the new company.        
	The board has also been reconstituted.         
	Three new directors have joined the Texmaco board. They are Utsav Parekh, Dipankar Chatterji and Gautam Khaitan.         
	Chairman Saroj Poddar, his son Akshay and H. Sadhak, the nominee director of the Life Insurance Corporation, will continue to be on the Texmaco board.        
	Six directors of Texmaco have opted to resign and join Texmaco Rail. They are A.C. Chakrabortti, Manish Gupta, S. Dhasarathy, B. P. Bajoria, Ramesh Maheshwari and D. H. Kela.        
	Saroj Poddar has been co-opted on the board of the new company.        
	The record date for the demerger will be announced as soon as the certified copy from Calcutta High Court is available.        
	Meanwhile, Saroj Poddar said he expected a final approval on a Delhi realty project soon. Texmaco is hoping to develop over a million square feet at a prime location in Delhi.                                                                                                                                       
